message:
Hello,

We are implementing webhook consumption in our application and having trouble verifying the HMAC-SHA256 signatures. We are using Node.js and the crypto module.

Our verification code:
```
const crypto = require('crypto');
const signature = req.headers['x-techcorp-signature'];
const hash = crypto.createHmac('sha256', webhookSecret).update(req.body).digest('hex');
if (signature !== hash) { // always fails }
```

The signature never matches. We have double-checked our webhook secret. Are we using the correct header name? Is the request body raw or parsed?

Documentation on webhook verification seems sparse.

Andrew Mitchell
Backend Developer, Quantum Software
